adle, JUnit tests","messageBody":"","tags":["Level-9","A-TextUiTesting","A-MoreOOP","A-JavaDoc","A-CodingStandard"],"fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"gradle":{"insertions":3,"deletions":1},"java":{"insertions":193,"deletions":1}}}]},{"date":"2026-03-01T00:00:00","commitResults":[{"hash":"981496878424825fb83e60a542cd495282f38b56","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Checkstyle","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"gradle":{"insertions":5,"deletions":2},"java":{"insertions":126,"deletions":116}}}]},{"date":"2026-03-02T00:00:00","commitResults":[{"hash":"3e34e84ab85c1be4d7558b579bef89e24701706a","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Level 10: GUI","messageBody":"","tags":["Level-10","A-Jar"],"fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"gradle":{"insertions":16,"deletions":2},"fxml":{"insertions":35,"deletions":0},"txt":{"insertions":0,"deletions":0},"java":{"insertions":292,"deletions":138},"bat":{"insertions":0,"deletions":21},"sh":{"insertions":0,"deletions":38}}}]},{"date":"2026-03-08T00:00:00","commitResults":[{"hash":"493e9b5b9991588a26636830935f94fe7ac00c67","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Add assertions to document internal assumptions","messageBody":"Certain internal methods and constructors have implicit assumptions\nabout their arguments, such as being non-null or adhering to specific\nformats.\n\nUnverified assumptions can lead to bugs that are hard to trace and\ndebug when unexpected values are passed internally.\n\nLet\u0027s,\n* add assertions in Perlica.java to verify correct command types and\n  non-null inputs\n* add assertions in Storage.java to ensure parsed lines are not null\n* add assertions in DateParser.java to enforce valid date inputs\n* add assertions in Task.java to ensure task descriptions are not null\n\nUsing assertions explicitly documents these assumptions and ensures\nthey are validated during development and testing without incurring\noverhead in production.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"java":{"insertions":7,"deletions":0}}},{"hash":"8ea29b0db262e5f4e5ac54fe6f0d141924bdd5dd","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Perlica class: Extract task creation methods","messageBody":"The [addTask()] method handles both the flow control and the string\nparsing for different tasks. This groups multiple abstraction levels\ntogether, reducing readability.\n\nLet\u0027s,\n* extract parsing logic for Todo into [createTodo()]\n* extract parsing logic for Deadline into [createDeadline()]\n* extract parsing logic for Event into [createEvent()]\n\nBy extracting these, we improve readability, separate the high-level\nlogic from the low-level string manipulation, and adhere better to the\nSingle Level of Abstraction Principle.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"java":{"insertions":36,"deletions":32}}},{"hash":"0ab745039d7569ae4e32d21508e3be79add48f89","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge pull request #2 from vietquang1006/branch-A-Assertions","messageBody":"Add assertions to document internal assumptions","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"e56caf42a7f16b635302a28651c1138889f6f86a","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge pull request #3 from vietquang1006/branch-A-CodeQuality","messageBody":"Perlica class: Extract task creation methods","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"3a543b0001c6570984aa667a8f7a238327b9c4fa","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge branch \u0027master\u0027 of https://github.com/vietquang1006/ip","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"689c2ef9166c6cab11e2af46b2b14e32e7c10d36","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"docs: Add User Guide to README.md","messageBody":"The project repository lacks detailed instructions on how to interact\nwith the application.\n\nNew users downloading or viewing the repository do not have a clear\nreference for the available commands, their expected formats, and\ntheir functions.\n\nLet\u0027s,\n* add a comprehensive User Guide section to the README.md\n* document the syntax and purpose of all supported commands\n\nPlacing the documentation directly in the README.md ensures it is\nimmediately visible to anyone visiting the repository page, making\nthe project more accessible and user-friendly.\n","tags":["A-UserGuide","A-CodeQuality","A-Assertions"],"fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"md":{"insertions":49,"deletions":42}}},{"hash":"b16638e210533936cf99e455e86ef20627a5cb17","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Refactor: Extract horizontal line to constant","messageBody":"The UI uses a hardcoded string of underscores for horizontal lines\nacross different methods and classes.\n\nDuplicating this string violates the DRY principle and makes UI\nmodifications tedious and prone to inconsistencies.\n\nLet\u0027s,\n* extract the underscore string into a HORIZONTAL_LINE constant\n* replace all hardcoded instances with this new variable\n\nA centralized constant ensures UI consistency and allows for easy,\nsingle-point updates to the line\u0027s appearance in the future.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"java":{"insertions":4,"deletions":2}}}]}]},"authorFileTypeContributionMap":{"vietquang1006":{"java":1041,"md":49,"fxml":35,"sh":0,"bat":0,"gradle":22,"txt":0}},"authorContributionVariance":{"vietquang1006":22583.771},"authorDisplayNameMap":{"vietquang1006":"CS2103T-W13-3 NGUY..UANG"}}
